                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/arth-215" class="program-course-title">
              ARTH 215 Introduction to East Asian Art (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18288" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Art History &amp; Communication Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Art History              : Introductory survey of some of the major developments in the visual arts of Japan, China, and Korea.  Emphasis will be placed on the diversity of artistic traditions in East Asia and the intersections among these traditions.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Jeffrey Moser (Fall)                  </p>

    
